      • descending

        public void descending(Class<?> declaringType,
                       Class<?> dependencyType,
                       Annotation[] typeAnnotations,
                       Annotation[] referenceAnnotations)
        Description copied from interface: ComponentContainer.Observer
        Notifies the receiver that a dependency is being resolved. Calls to this method are balanced by calls to ascending().
        Specified by:
        descending in interface ComponentContainer.Observer
        Parameters:
        declaringType - the class having the dependency to the dependencyType.
        dependencyType - the class with which the declaringType references the dependency.
        typeAnnotations - the annotations of the declaring class, and the constructor or method involved in the dependency, if any; may be null.
        referenceAnnotations - the annotations of the dependency reference; may be null.

      • circular

        public void circular(DependencyPath path)
        Description copied from interface: ComponentContainer.Observer
        Notifies the receiver that a loop has been detected in the dependency graph. Invoked for static dependencies only and at the point when the loop refers back to a component in the dependency path. The DependencyPath.tail() returns the component that depends on another in its reference path.
        Specified by:
        circular in interface ComponentContainer.Observer
        Parameters:
        path - the dependency path that is circular.

      • resolved

        public void resolved(DependencyPath path,
                     Class<?> type)
        Description copied from interface: ComponentContainer.Observer
        Notifies the receiver that a dependency has been resolved. Elements of the path are reference declarations and might not be the actual classes that will be instantiated for those references.
        Specified by:
        resolved in interface ComponentContainer.Observer
        Parameters:
        path - the dependency path at which the given type has been resolved.
        type - the type that has been resolved at the given dependency path.

      • instantiated

        public void instantiated(DependencyPath path,
                         AtomicReference<?> reference)
        Description copied from interface: ComponentContainer.Observer
        Notifies the receiver that a dependency has been instantiated. The path is final; elements of the path are actual classes that will be.

        The DependencyPath.tail() returns details about the just instantiated component.

        Specified by:
        instantiated in interface ComponentContainer.Observer
        Parameters:
        path - the dependency path at which the given type has been instantiated.
        reference - a reference to the component that has just been instantiated. The reference will be set after this method returns to prevent the receiver from wreaking havoc by accessing the just instantiated component.
